This paper is primarily focused on network functions and their virtualization, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The use of machine learning for auto-scaling is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the impact of different virtualization technologies on QoS and cost savings, which could be classified under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The use of machine learning for proactive scaling decisions could also be classified under control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of auto-scaling on security and privacy, which could be classified under cryptography and security (cs.CR).
